s, and clean-technology pioneers, Cohan identifies flaws in previous efforts to combat climate change. He highlights opportunities for more successful strategies, including international “climate clubs” and accelerated development of clean energy technologies. Grounded in history and emerging scholarship, this book offers a forward-looking vision of solutions to confronting climate gridlock and a clear-eyed recognition of the challenges to enacting them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aClimatic changesxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aClimatic changesxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh1 aWebber, Michael E.1 aWebber, Michael E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074977940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300265057?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300265057423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300265057/original  a978-3-11-074977-9  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099451-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-PLWb2022